    <h1>DOSING</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200808/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-08"><time>2020-08-08</time></a>
        - <span>TOP OF THE NEWS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Be­fore the vac­ci­na­tion is given, vol­un­teers un­dergo an­other round DOSING of ba­sic health checks.</p>
    <p>Af­ter the in­jec­tion is given in the arm, they are mon­i­tored for about four hours at the SingHealth In­ves­ti­ga­tional Medicine Unit (IMU) at the Sin­ga­pore Gen­eral Hos­pi­tal, be­fore be­ing dis­charged.</p>
    <p>They must record any changes or side ef­fects, and mon­i­tor the sever­ity of any symp­toms, such as headaches or mus­cle aches, on a three-point scale of mild, mod­er­ate or se­vere.</p>
    <p>The prin­ci­pal in­ves­ti­ga­tor and co­or­di­na­tor is on call 24 hours a day, in case symp­toms be­come se­vere.</p>

